# Never Clear the Database

When publishing the SpacetimeDB module, **NEVER** use the `--clear-database` flag.

```bash
# ❌ WRONG — destroys all user data
spacetime publish opencord --clear-database -y --module-path ./spacetimedb

# ✅ CORRECT — preserves existing data
spacetime publish opencord --module-path ./spacetimedb
```

This applies to all publish commands regardless of target server (local or maincloud). User data must be preserved across deploys.
